casebody.data:
Collins et al., Appellants, v. Down River Specialties, Inc. et al., Appellees.

[Cite as Collins v. Down River Specialties, Inc. (1999), 85 Ohio St.3d 1215.]

(Nos. 98-1099 and 98-1107 Submitted April 13, 1999 Decided May 26, 1999.) McLaughlin & McCaffrey, L.L.P., Patrick M. McLaughlin and John F. McCaffrey, for appellant Gertrude Collins. Jeffries, Kube, Forrest & Monteleone Co., L.P.A., and David A. Forrest, for appellant Kenneth Wilkerson. Stanley S. Keller and Brian D. Spitz, for appellees.

The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur. F.E. Sweeney, J., dissents and would reverse the judgment of the court of appeals.
